-- P&G sells PHA technology to Meredian
-- 
-- Thu Oct 4, 2007 2:30pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/04/us-pandg-acquisition-meredian-idUSWNAS558420071004

 

 (Reuters) - Procter & Gamble Co ( PG.N ) said it sold its Polyhydroxyalkanoate (PHA) technology to privately held Meredian Inc, which will use the technology to make new biopolymers using renewable resources. 

 Meredian plans to produce over 600 million pounds of biopolymers annually, the consumer products company added. (Reporting by Aniruddha Basu in Bangalore)